Reasoning: The paper discusses the issue of disappearing web resources and proposes a solution using social link neighborhood and tweet signatures. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). However, since the paper focuses on web archiving and resource availability, cs.IR and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of tweet signatures and Topsy API also suggests a focus on social media and information retrieval, further supporting the choice of cs.IR and cs.SI as the top two sub-categories.
